-- Deutsche Post Rivals Want Stricter Regulation, FTD Reports
-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 2011-12-22T06:54:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-22/deutsche-post-rivals-want-stricter-regulation-ftd-reports.html
Deutsche Post AG (DPW) ’s rivals demanded
that  Germany  introduce stricter regulation in the postal
industry to increase competition, the  Financial Times
Deutschland  reported today, citing the BBD postal association.  The BBD also urged the government to sell the Deutsche Post
stake that KfW Group, Germany’s state-owned development bank,
still holds, the newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
